1. Create a new project using the "Godot" template.
2. Set up the scene by adding a CanvasBackground node and placing the main camera and other scene elements.
3. Create a base class for your game called "Game" (e.g., "MainGame").
4. Extend the "Node" class in the "Game" class to make it a Node so it can be used as a scene node.
5. Use signals and slots to handle events, such as user input, scene logic, and rendering.

